TextDocument.fillColor <L=Z#1n></L><I=1n>
 textDocument.fillColor 

Description <L=Z#1o></L><I=1o>
The Text layer's fill color, as an array of  [r, g, b]  floating-point values. For example, in an 8-bpc
project, a red value of 255 would be 1.0, and in a 32-bpc project, an overbright blue value can be
something like 3.2.

Throws an exception on read if <L=Z#8>applyFill</L> is not  true  .

Setting this value will also set <L=Z#8>applyFill</L> to  true  across the affected characters.

Warning

This value only reflects the first character in the Text layer.

If you change this value, it will set all characters in the Text layer to the specified setting.

Type <L=Z#1p></L><I=1p>
Array  [r, g, b]  of floating-point values; read/write.

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

